    "body": "As a temporary solution, it's perhaps best to wrap syncProgress in a Swift Enum that is set to .unknown at the start or assume syncProgress is unknown at the start. If you happen to catch a non nil syncProgress later, you can update the enum. Alternatively, compare the last block number Geth returns to a known Ethereum stats site.\r\n\r\nUltimately, it would make sense to have Geth return an enum and support a delegate callback.",
